==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acid process
<hw>Ac"id proc"ess</hw>. <fld>(Iron Metal.)</fld> <def>That variety of
either the Bessemer or the open-hearth process in which the converter or
hearth is lined with acid, that is, highly siliceous, material. Opposed
to <contr>basic process</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acidulate</ent>⟦br⟧
